entries.next: You again? Well then, I guess I can let you look around some more. Go on in.
entries.cantwork: Sorry, this is a private family retreat. Can't let you in unless you have an invitation. Funny, you look too busy to enjoy the place.
entries.npc_reset_1: All right, I understand. I hope you'll check back later when you're ready.
entries.notyet: Sorry, I need some time alone.
entries.npc_1_1: Sorry, this is a private family retreat. You can go in if you have an invitation. Otherwise -- well then, you might make yourself useful. Want a job? A Corellian visitor brought in a pet krahbu -- one of those big, fast mount animals -- and it got loose. Something drove it crazy -- maybe when it ate the local plants. Now this pet is killing local wildlife and livestock. Find the krahbu and kill it.
entries.npc_2_1: Good. I'll wait for you here. Come on back after you've put down the krahbu. Be careful.
entries.npc_3_1: Well then. I expect you'll find some nice place to visit, other than here. Goodbye.
entries.npc_4_1: This is the Lake Retreat of the Naberrie family, one of the most honored families in Naboo history. Queen Padme Amidala was a Naberrie, along with several former senators and many high officials. Now, about that job --
entries.npc_backtowork_1: I've got nothing more to tell you about that krahbu. Get to it.
entries.npc_reward_1: Sorry to see that animal put down, but it had to be done. Invading species, you know. Here's a reward. If you have an invitation, go right in. Otherwise -- well then, talk to me about another little job, and after that, I'd be willing to let you in to look around.
entries.npc_work_1: Hmm, didn't expect you back. Not yet done putting down that krahbu, I see. Well then, get to it.
entries.npc_noloc_1: That's good -- no, wait. I remember, I've got a tour group ambling through that area just now. This would be a bad time to kill animals there. Check back with me later.
entries.npc_failure_1: Couldn't catch that krahbu, eh? I'm not surprised, they're fast. Well, thanks anyway.
entries.player_reset_1: I don't want this mission right now.
entries.player_sorry_1: I'll keep working on the mission.
entries.npc_1_2: Interested in more work, are you? Well then, if you take care of one more little matter, I'll let you into the retreat -- assuming you don't have an invitation already. I think that krahbu infected a local mott with some Corellian virus. The disease must have driven the thing crazy. You have to put it down before the epidemic spreads.
entries.npc_2_2: Good. I'll be here waiting, just like before. Come on back after you've put down the mott.
entries.npc_3_2: And you made yourself so useful before. Guess that was the exception. Well then, goodbye.
entries.npc_4_2: If you can picture a little garbage masher on four legs and covered with fur and tusks, that's a mott. Ill-tempered and brusque, in contrast to my own sweet nature. Well then, about this job -- will you take it?
entries.npc_backtowork_2: I've got nothing more to tell you about this mott. Get to it.
entries.npc_reward_2: Thanks. That mott was just a nuisance before, digging up my garden and whatnot. But this could have been a plague. Well then, you've proven you have gumption. Go on in, look around -- but don't tell anyone I let you in.
entries.npc_work_2: Hmm, didn't expect you back. Not yet done putting down that mott, I see. Well then, get to it.
entries.npc_noloc_2: That's good -- no, wait. I've got a tour group ambling through that area just now. This would be a bad time to kill animals there. Check back with me later.
entries.npc_failure_2: Couldn't catch those mott, eh? I'm not surprised, they're sneaky. Well, thanks anyway.
entries.player_reset_2: I don't want this mission right now.
entries.player_sorry_2: I'll keep working on the mission.
